<subSubSection id="219A81E3FF82A45AFF17F867FF74FE9B" lastPageId="25" lastPageNumber="26" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="693FD268FF82A45AFF17F867FF74FE9B" blockId="24.[151,1437,1905,2040]" lastBlockId="25.[151,1437,152,1116]" lastPageId="25" lastPageNumber="26" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis id="5BF40E7AFF82A45BFF17F867FE23F828" bold="true" box="[199,441,1977,2004]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Diagnosis of female.</emphasis>
Body narrow, about 2.5–3.5 times longer than wide; cephalon not immersed in pereonite 1, anterolateral margin concave, eyes present; pereonite 1 anterolateral margins minute or projecting laterally, anterior margin straight or slightly convex; pleonite 1 overlapped by pereonite 7, narrower than pleonites 2–5; antennula bases contiguous, peduncle articles 1–3 of similar size and bigger than other articles, peduncle articles 1–3 anterodistal margins produced, terminal articles without setae; coxae not overlapping adjacent pereonites; mandible articles 1–3 articulated; maxilla with welldefined medial and lateral lobes; maxilliped palp article 3 apex with multiple recurved spines; pereopods 5–7 basis with raised carina uropod rami not extending beyond pleotelson posterior margin.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="219A81E3FF83A45AFF17FEAFFE47FBA0" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="693FD268FF83A45AFF17FEAFFD06FD9F" blockId="25.[151,1437,152,1116]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis id="5BF40E7AFF83A45AFF17FEAFFEA1FE77" bold="true" box="[199,315,369,395]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="0D11AF99FF83A45AFE93FEAFFDA9FE77" author="Martin, M. B. &amp; Bruce, N. L. &amp; Nowak, B. F." box="[323,563,368,395]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="337 - 350" refId="ref75352" refString="Martin, M. B., Bruce, N. L. &amp; Nowak, B. F. (2015 b) Review of the buccal-attaching fish parasite genus Glossobius Schioedte &amp; Meinert, 1883 (Crustacea, Isopoda, Cymothoidae). Zootaxa, 3973 (2), 337 - 350. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3973.2.8" type="journal article" year="2015">
Martin 
<emphasis id="5BF40E7AFF83A45AFE48FEACFE48FE77" box="[408,466,369,395]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">et al.</emphasis>
(2015b)
</bibRefCitation>
provided a provisional diagnosis. 
<taxonomicName id="AE80A9EBFF83A45AFC6BFEAFFBADFE77" authorityName="Schioedte &amp; Meinert" authorityYear="1883" box="[955,1079,369,395]" class="Malacostraca" family="Cymothoidae" genus="Glossobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5BF40E7AFF83A45AFC6BFEAFFBADFE77" box="[955,1079,369,395]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Glossobius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be recognized by the body strongly vaulted; cephalon not being immersed in pereonite 1; antenna bases in contact, antennula subequal to antenna; mandible palp article 2 longer than article 3; maxilla medial lobe distinct; maxillula with 3–5 or more terminal spines; maxilliped article with 2 oostegite lobes; pereonite 1 anterolateral margins minute or projecting laterally, anterior margin straight or slightly convex; pleonite 1 overlapped by pereonite 7, narrower than pleonites 2–5; brood pouch from coxae 1–4 and 6; uropod rami shorter than pleotelson, rami exopod shorter than endopod. Species of 
<taxonomicName id="AE80A9EBFF83A45AFF47FD97FE89FD9F" authorityName="Schioedte &amp; Meinert" authorityYear="1883" box="[151,275,585,611]" class="Malacostraca" family="Cymothoidae" genus="Glossobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5BF40E7AFF83A45AFF47FD97FE89FD9F" box="[151,275,585,611]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Glossobius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are restricted to beloniform fishes.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="693FD268FF83A45AFF17FDB3FE9EFC37" blockId="25.[151,1437,152,1116]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
Recently 
<bibRefCitation id="0D11AF99FF83A45AFEE4FDB3FDB2FD7B" author="Martin, M. B. &amp; Bruce, N. L. &amp; Nowak, B. F." box="[308,552,620,647]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="337 - 350" refId="ref75352" refString="Martin, M. B., Bruce, N. L. &amp; Nowak, B. F. (2015 b) Review of the buccal-attaching fish parasite genus Glossobius Schioedte &amp; Meinert, 1883 (Crustacea, Isopoda, Cymothoidae). Zootaxa, 3973 (2), 337 - 350. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3973.2.8" type="journal article" year="2015">
Martin 
<emphasis id="5BF40E7AFF83A45AFE5AFDB0FE5FFD7B" box="[394,453,621,647]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">et al.</emphasis>
(2015b)
</bibRefCitation>
reviewed the genus 
<taxonomicName id="AE80A9EBFF83A45AFCC9FDB3FC0FFD7B" authorityName="Schioedte &amp; Meinert" authorityYear="1883" box="[793,917,621,647]" class="Malacostraca" family="Cymothoidae" genus="Glossobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5BF40E7AFF83A45AFCC9FDB3FC0FFD7B" box="[793,917,621,647]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Glossobius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="119792F8FF83A45AFC0EFDB3FBD2FD7B" box="[990,1096,621,647]" name="Australia" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Australia</collectingCountry>
. 
<taxonomicName id="AE80A9EBFF83A45AFB85FDB3FB4BFD7B" authorityName="Schioedte &amp; Meinert" authorityYear="1883" box="[1109,1233,621,647]" class="Malacostraca" family="Cymothoidae" genus="Glossobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5BF40E7AFF83A45AFB85FDB3FB4BFD7B" box="[1109,1233,621,647]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Glossobius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differ from other buccal attaching genera in the following characterstics: 
<taxonomicName id="AE80A9EBFF83A45AFCD1FD4FFC1BFD57" authorityName="Dana" authorityYear="1852" box="[769,897,657,683]" class="Malacostraca" family="Cymothoidae" genus="Ceratothoa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5BF40E7AFF83A45AFCD1FD4FFC1BFD57" box="[769,897,657,683]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Ceratothoa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
pereonite 1 anterolateral margins projecting forward; pereonite 6 longer than 
<taxonomicName id="AE80A9EBFF83A45AFE37FD6BFDF9FD33" authorityName="Schioedte &amp; Meinert" authorityYear="1883" box="[487,611,693,719]" class="Malacostraca" family="Cymothoidae" genus="Glossobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5BF40E7AFF83A45AFE37FD6BFDF9FD33" box="[487,611,693,719]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Glossobius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; anterior margin of pereonite 1 indented (
<bibRefCitation id="0D11AF99FF83A45AFBE6FD6BFADFFD33" author="Bruce, N. L. &amp; Bowman, T. E." box="[1078,1349,693,719]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="1 - 28" refId="ref71499" refString="Bruce, N. L. &amp; Bowman, T. E. (1989) Species of the parasitic isopod genera Ceratothoa and Glossobius (Crustacea, Cymothoidae) from the mouths of flying fishes and halfbeaks (Beloniformes). Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology, 489, 1 - 28. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00810282.489" type="journal article" year="1989">Bruce &amp; Bowman 1989</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="0D11AF99FF83A45AFA80FD6BFEBAFD0F" author="Martin, M. B. &amp; Bruce, N. L. &amp; Nowak, B. F." pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="337 - 350" refId="ref75352" refString="Martin, M. B., Bruce, N. L. &amp; Nowak, B. F. (2015 b) Review of the buccal-attaching fish parasite genus Glossobius Schioedte &amp; Meinert, 1883 (Crustacea, Isopoda, Cymothoidae). Zootaxa, 3973 (2), 337 - 350. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3973.2.8" type="journal article" year="2015">
Martin 
<emphasis id="5BF40E7AFF83A45AFF47FD04FF55FD0F" box="[151,207,729,755]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">et al.</emphasis>
2015b
</bibRefCitation>
); 
<taxonomicName id="AE80A9EBFF83A45AFEE3FD07FD21FD0F" authority="Schioedte &amp; Meinert, 1884" authorityName="Schioedte &amp; Meinert" authorityYear="1884" box="[307,699,729,755]" class="Malacostraca" family="Cymothoidae" genus="Cinusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5BF40E7AFF83A45AFEE3FD07FE18FD0F" box="[307,386,729,755]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Cinusa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="0D11AF99FF83A45AFE58FD07FD21FD0F" author="Schioedte, J. C. &amp; Meinert, F." box="[392,699,729,755]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="221 - 454" refId="ref79494" refString="Schioedte, J. C. &amp; Meinert, F. (1884) Symbolae ad monographium Cymothoarum crustaceorum isopodum familiae. IV. Cymothoidae Trib. II. Cymothoinae. Trib. III: Lironecinae. Naturhistorisk Tidsskrift, 14, 221 - 454." type="journal article" year="1884">Schiöedte &amp; Meinert, 1884</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
: pereonites 3 and 4 widest anteriorly; antenna slender (
<bibRefCitation id="0D11AF99FF83A45AFACEFD07FF63FCEB" author="Hadfield, K. A. &amp; Bruce, N. L. &amp; Smit, N. J." pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="51 - 68" refId="ref72766" refString="Hadfield, K. A., Bruce, N. L. &amp; Smit, N. J. (2010) Redescription of the monotypic genus Cinusa Schioedte &amp; Meinert, 1884 (Isopoda, Cymothoidae), a buccal-cavity isopod from South Africa. Zootaxa, 2437 (1), 51 - 68. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 2437.1.3" type="journal article" year="2010">
Hadfield 
<emphasis id="5BF40E7AFF83A45AFA58FD04FF2EFCEB" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">et al.</emphasis>
2010
</bibRefCitation>
); brood pouch arising from coxae 2–5 (
<bibRefCitation id="0D11AF99FF83A45AFD69FD23FCF8FCEB" author="Hadfield, K. A." box="[697,866,765,791]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" refId="ref72724" refString="Hadfield, K. A. (2012) The biodiversity and systematics of marine fish parasitic isopods of the family Cymothoidae from southern Africa. Faculty of Science, Philosophiae Doctor, University of Johannesberg, Johannesberg, 445 pp." type="book" year="2012">Hadfield 2012</bibRefCitation>
); 
<taxonomicName id="AE80A9EBFF83A45AFCA6FD23FC73FCEB" authorityName="Mathoei Leach" authorityYear="1818" box="[886,1001,765,791]" class="Malacostraca" family="Cymothoidae" genus="Cymothoa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5BF40E7AFF83A45AFCA6FD23FC73FCEB" box="[886,1001,765,791]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Cymothoa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
strongly vaulted body, coxae partially visible dorsally, pereonite 7 posterolateral margins extending past pleonite 1; and pleopods 3–5 with large fleshy folds (
<bibRefCitation id="0D11AF99FF83A45AFF0EFC9BFE31FC9C" author="Martin, M. B. &amp; Bruce, N. L. &amp; Nowak, B. F." box="[222,427,837,864]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="1" refId="ref75420" refString="Martin, M. B., Bruce, N. L. &amp; Nowak, B. F. (2016) Review of the fish-parasitic genus Cymothoa Fabricius, 1793 (Crustacea, Isopoda, Cymothoidae) from Australia. Zootaxa, 4119 (1), 001 - 072. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4119.1.1" type="journal article" year="2016">
Martin 
<emphasis id="5BF40E7AFF83A45AFEE4FC98FEFCFCA3" box="[308,358,837,863]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">et al</emphasis>
2016
</bibRefCitation>
); 
<taxonomicName id="AE80A9EBFF83A45AFE6FFC9BFD70FCA3" authority="Bleeker, 1857" authorityName="Bleeker" authorityYear="1857" box="[447,746,836,863]" class="Malacostraca" family="Cymothoidae" genus="Lobothorax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5BF40E7AFF83A45AFE6FFC9BFDD8FCA3" box="[447,578,837,863]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Lobothorax</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="0D11AF99FF83A45AFD99FC9BFD70FCA3" author="Bleeker, P." box="[585,746,836,863]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="20 - 40" refId="ref70402" refString="Bleeker, P. (1857) Recherches sur les Crustaces de l'Inde archipelagique. II. Sur les Isopodes Cymothoadiens de l'archipel Indien. Natuurkundige Vereeniging in Nederlandsch-Indie, Batavia, Verhandelingen, 2, 20 - 40." type="journal article" year="1857">Bleeker, 1857</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
: pereonite 1 anterolateral margins rounded, with strongly developed lobes, dorsally concave and flattened, extending past rostrum (
<bibRefCitation id="0D11AF99FF83A45AFC77FCB7FBF5FC78" author="Yu, H. Y. &amp; Bruce, N. L." box="[935,1135,873,900]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="641 - 648" refId="ref82484" refString="Yu, H. Y. &amp; Bruce, N. L. (2006) Redescription of Lobothorax typus Bleeker, 1857 (Isopoda: Cymothoidae), The first record of the species and genus from Chinese waters. Crustaceana, 79, 641 - 648. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 156854006778026816" type="journal article" year="2006">Yu &amp; Bruce 2006</bibRefCitation>
); and 
<taxonomicName id="AE80A9EBFF83A45AFB7FFCB7FF49FC5B" authority="Ozdikmen, 2009" authorityName="Ozdikmen" authorityYear="2009" class="Malacostraca" family="Cymothoidae" genus="Smenispa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5BF40E7AFF83A45AFB7FFCB7FA80FC7F" box="[1199,1306,873,899]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Smenispa</emphasis>
Özdikmen, 2009
</taxonomicName>
: pleopods 3–5 have large folds, and pereon and pleon are co-linear with subparallel lateral margins (
<bibRefCitation id="0D11AF99FF83A45AFAE3FC53FF62FC37" author="Martin, M. B. &amp; Bruce, N. L. &amp; Nowak, B. F." pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="233 - 240" refId="ref75207" refString="Martin, M. B., Bruce, N. L. &amp; Nowak, B. F. (2014) Smenispa irregularis (Bleeker, 1857) (Crustacea: Isopoda: Cymothoidae), a, buccal-attaching fish parasite from Australia. Records of the Australian Museum, 66, 233 - 240. https: // doi. org / 10.3853 / j. 2201 - 4349.66.2014.160" type="journal article" year="2014">
Martin 
<emphasis id="5BF40E7AFF83A45AFA58FC50FF2EFC37" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">et al.</emphasis>
2014
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="693FD268FF83A45AFF17FC0BFE47FBA0" blockId="25.[151,1437,152,1116]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
To date, the genus 
<taxonomicName id="AE80A9EBFF83A45AFE71FC0BFCF2FC13" authority="Schioedte &amp; Meinert (1883)" authorityName="Schioedte &amp; Meinert" authorityYear="1883" box="[417,872,981,1007]" class="Malacostraca" family="Cymothoidae" genus="Glossobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5BF40E7AFF83A45AFE71FC0BFD87FC13" box="[417,541,981,1007]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Glossobius</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="0D11AF99FF83A45AFDF6FC0BFCF2FC13" author="Schioedte, J. C. &amp; Meinert, F." box="[550,872,981,1007]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="281 - 378" refId="ref79456" refString="Schioedte, J. C. &amp; Meinert, F. (1883) Symbolae ad monographium Cymothoarum crustaeorum isopodum familiae III. Saophridae. IV. Cerathoinae. Naturhistorisk Tidsskrift, 13, 281 - 378." type="journal article" year="1883">Schiöedte &amp; Meinert (1883)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
includes eight valid species (WoRMS, 2018). Of this three species of the genus have been reported from Indian waters, namely, 
<taxonomicName id="AE80A9EBFF83A45AFBDAFC27FA02FBEF" authority="Bovallius, 1885" authorityName="Bovallius" authorityYear="1885" box="[1034,1432,1016,1043]" class="Malacostraca" family="Cymothoidae" genus="Glossobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="auritus">
<emphasis id="5BF40E7AFF83A45AFBDAFC27FB47FBEF" box="[1034,1245,1017,1043]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Glossobius auritus</emphasis>
Bovallius, 1885
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="AE80A9EBFF83A45AFF47FBC3FD73FBCB" authority="Williams &amp; Williams, 1985" authorityName="Williams &amp; Williams" authorityYear="1985" box="[151,745,1052,1079]" class="Malacostraca" family="Cymothoidae" genus="Glossobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hemiramphi">
<emphasis id="5BF40E7AFF83A45AFF47FBC3FE3EFBCB" box="[151,420,1053,1079]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Glossobius hemiramphi</emphasis>
Williams &amp; Williams, 1985
</taxonomicName>
(Aneesh 
<emphasis id="5BF40E7AFF83A45AFC8AFBC0FC0EFBCB" box="[858,916,1053,1079]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">et al.</emphasis>
2017) and 
<taxonomicName id="AE80A9EBFF83A45AFBCAFBC3FE43FBA0" authority="(Say, 1818) (Vigneshwaran et al. 2018 b)" authorityName="Vigneshwaran et al." authorityYear="2018" baseAuthorityName="Say" baseAuthorityYear="1818" class="Malacostraca" family="Cymothoidae" genus="Glossobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="impressus">
<emphasis id="5BF40E7AFF83A45AFBCAFBC3FA95FBCB" box="[1050,1295,1053,1079]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Glossobius impressus</emphasis>
(Say, 1818) (
<bibRefCitation id="0D11AF99FF83A45AFF4FFB9FFE48FBA0" author="Vigneshwaran, P. &amp; Ravichandran, S &amp; Rameshkumar, G." box="[159,466,1089,1116]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="1403 - 1407" refId="ref81534" refString="Vigneshwaran, P., Ravichandran, S &amp; Rameshkumar, G. (2018 b) Glossobius impressus (Say, 1818) (Isopoda, Cymothoidae), a buccal-attaching fish parasite new to India. Crustaceana, 91 (11), 1403 - 1407. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 15685403 - 00003843" type="journal article" year="2018">
Vigneshwaran 
<emphasis id="5BF40E7AFF83A45AFE98FB9CFE1AFBA7" box="[328,384,1089,1115]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">et al.</emphasis>
2018b
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
